&lt;li&gt;Collaborate cross-functionally with product management, business development, and engineering teams to identify and develop new markets, products, and technologies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support creation of technical proposals and white papers that articulate the differentiation and mission utility of Muon’s offerings.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;B.S., M.S., or Ph.D. in Physics, Remote Sensing, Earth Science, Computer Science, Engineering, or a related technical/scientific field.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5+ years of experience in geospatial research, analysis, and imagery data product development.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong foundation in scientific first principles, including geospatial imagery analysis, spectral science, optical systems, and physics-based remote sensing.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Background in infrared, multispectral, hyperspectral, or similar remote sensing phenomenologies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated proficiency in programming (e.g., Python, MATLAB, Julia) for advanced image processing and geospatial analysis.&lt;/li&gt;
