&lt;li&gt;Research, design, and implement scalable algorithms for image mosaicking, orthorectification, and radiometric normalization of multispectral infrared imagery.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Product owner for critical customer-facing imagery products in the SBEM and FireSat programs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Author and maintain technical and customer-facing design documents for imagery products, ensuring alignment between internal capabilities and external stakeholder requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Engage with customer technical stakeholders including Technical Interchange Meetings (TIMs), customer questions, and program meetings&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Write production-ready code that integrates into customer-facing data product pipelines and operational services.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure the scientific quality, quantitative validation, and integrity of Orthomosaic Tile products across both wildfire and SBEM missions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work cross-functionally with software engineers, calibration scientists, and instrument engineers to design, build, and maintain operational data product services.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Learn new topics as needed (e.g., sensor geometry and characterization, georeferencing techniques, wildfire and environmental monitoring applications, cloud-native geospatial data engineering).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
